<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1167067141971"><term>Big Bang</term><meaning id="fs-id1167066790853">a gigantic explosion that threw out matter a few billion years ago</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167066880808"><term>Electroweak Epoch</term><meaning id="fs-id1167061217473">the stage before 10<sup>−11</sup> back to 10<sup>−34</sup> seconds after the Big Bang</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167066867244"><term>electroweak theory</term><meaning id="fs-id1167067314145">theory showing connections between EM and weak forces</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167066971686"><term>Grand Unification Epoch</term><meaning id="fs-id1167067314416">the time period from 10<sup>−43</sup> to 10<sup>−34</sup> seconds after the Big Bang, when Grand Unification Theory, in which all forces except gravity are identical, governed the universe</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167063816922"><term>Grand Unified Theory</term><meaning id="fs-id1167063720067">theory that shows unification of the strong and electroweak forces</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167063583188"><term>Inflationary Epoch</term><meaning id="fs-id1167067069451">the rapid expansion of the universe by an incredible factor of 10<sup>−50</sup> for the brief time from 10<sup>−35</sup> to about 10<sup>−32</sup> seconds</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167067073155"><term>Planck Epoch</term><meaning id="fs-id1167066800711">the earliest era of the universe, before 10<sup>–43</sup> seconds after the Big Bang</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167067110124"><term>Quark Era</term><meaning id="fs-id1167067007582">the time period from 10<sup>–11</sup> to 10<sup>–6</sup> seconds at which all four fundamental forces are separated and quarks begin to exit</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167061608149"><term>superforce</term><meaning id="fs-id1167067023567">the unification of all four fundamental forces into one force</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167067019539"><term>Theory of Everything</term><meaning id="fs-id1167066879551">the theory that shows unification of all four fundamental forces</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
